# Cicero Web Studio environment variables
#
# Local development:
#   npm run env:setup    # copies this file to .env (if missing)
#   Fill in values, then: npm run env:check
#
# Vercel (single source of truth for production):
#   Pull:  npm run env:pull
#   Push:  Vercel dashboard → Project Settings → Environment Variables → Import .env
#
# Security:
#   - Never commit .env (it is gitignored)
#   - Never prefix secrets with VITE_ (those are bundled into the browser)
#   - RESEND_API_KEY, GOOGLE_SHEETS_WEBHOOK_SECRET stay server-side only

# --- Client (VITE_ = exposed to browser; safe for anon keys only) ---
